A query for `et` keeps multiple existing matches and also allows a new session.
The new-session row is selectable, so `M-up` jumps to that row.

    :k et
    :snap

```terminal
session: et                                                                                        ┃
  3/6 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close                                                             ┃
   et                                                                                              ┃
▌⬤ beta                                                                                            ┃
